Name: Thomas Jestopher 🌋⚡⬛👾
Tweet: The sats (💰) cost of a 🔋 depends on the mempool (🎱) condition, which is measured in sats/vByte or 💰/🍆.🎱 = 💰/🍆In essence, 🔋=~300🍆*🎱Today, because 🎱=1, you can get a 🔋 for 300💰.

Name: Thomas Jestopher 🌋⚡⬛👾
Tweet: It's about 150 bytes (🍆) to open (🙌🏾) or close(🙏🏿) a channel 🔋 and it requires both 🙌🏾+🙏🏿 to make a 🔋 work. ~150🍆= 🙌🏾=🙏🏿Therefore, 🙌🏾+🙏🏿= ~300🍆That's 300 🍆 times the mempool (🎱) condition (💰/🍆) over the life of the channel (🔋).🙌🏾+🙏🏿=🔋300🍆*🎱=🔋

Name: Thomas Jestopher 🌋⚡⬛👾
Tweet: Four 1M sat balanced channels 🔋🔋🔋🔋will provide 2M sats of inbound ⚡. You only get half because 50% of each 🔋's capacity is your bitcoin (aka local balance 💦). 🔋🔋🔋🔋 @ 50% =⚡⚡+💦💦

Name: Thomas Jestopher 🌋⚡⬛👾
Tweet: The 💰 case for #LightningNetwork:Say you make 4 balanced channels (🔋) to  provide liquidity to one destination. The inbound (+⚡) from the 4 balanced channels (+⚡/-💦) will need to equal the liquidity -💦 provided to the one destination (🔦) e.g. LOOP.🔦+💦💦=🔋🔋🔋🔋-⚡⚡
